# DOM Day 4 - Changing Styles with JavaScript

## Topics Learned
- style.color
- style.backgroundColor
- style.fontSize
- style.display

---

## Change Text Color

```javascript
document.querySelector("#title").style.color = "red";
```

Changes the text color of the selected element.

---

## Change Background Color

```javascript
document.body.style.backgroundColor = "blue";
```

Changes the page background color.

---

## Change Font Size

```javascript
document.querySelector("#title").style.fontSize = "50px";
```

Changes the size of the text.

---

## Hide an Element

```javascript
document.querySelector("#title").style.display = "none";
```

Hides the selected element.

---

## Show an Element

```javascript
document.querySelector("#title").style.display = "block";
```

Makes the hidden element visible again.

---

## Key Takeaways

- JavaScript can modify CSS styles.
- `style.color` changes text color.
- `style.backgroundColor` changes background color.
- `style.fontSize` changes text size.
- `style.display` can hide or show elements.

